</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="707" pageNumber="708" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="707" pageNumber="708">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Glanodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="707" pageNumber="708" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puncticeps">Glanodes puncticeps</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1914: 61. Type locality: &quot;Peach Spring[s] [Mohave County], Arizona&quot; (original citation). Lectotype [as holotype] (♀), designated by Ball (1972: 192), in USNM [# 47735].
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="707" pageNumber="708">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ball" authorityYear="1973" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="707" pageNumber="708" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cunctipeps">Harpalus cunctipeps</taxonomicName>
Ball, 1973: 74. Replacement name for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Casey" baseAuthorityYear="1914" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="707" pageNumber="708" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puncticeps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="707" pageNumber="708">Harpalus puncticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Casey, 1914).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="707" pageNumber="708" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="707" pageNumber="708">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="707" pageNumber="708">This species is known only from northwestern Arizona [see Ball 1972: Fig. 13; Perrault 1982b: 269].</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
